The paper proposes a deep learning model for EEG-based intention recognition, which involves both spatial and temporal dependencies. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
